@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
# Run requests top-to-bottom so the session cookie is reused (VS Code REST Client / IntelliJ).
# Full automated run: node run-test-http.mjs

### Health (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

### DB check without login — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/db-check

### Login (test file uses Paolo)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "Paolo",
  "password": "Paolo123"
}

### Current user (use cookie from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/current

### DB check with session cookie
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/db-check

### Network full (setup map)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/network?view=full

### Network planning (stations only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/network?view=planning

### All segment pairs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/segments

### New game (setup)
# @name newGame
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/games

### Begin planning (random start/dest, 90s deadline)
# @name planning
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/games/{{newGame.response.body.id}}/planning

# Planning assigned: start={{planning.response.body.startStationId}} ({{planning.response.body.start}})
#                   dest={{planning.response.body.destinationStationId}} ({{planning.response.body.destination}})
# Before the next request, generate a valid route for THIS game (nodemon must be running):
#   node print-route-for-game.mjs {{newGame.response.body.id}}

### Submit route (reads route-body.json generated above)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/games/{{newGame.response.body.id}}/route
Content-Type: application/json

< route-body.json

### Get game state
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/games/{{newGame.response.body.id}}

### Ranking (best score per user)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/ranking

### Logout
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/current

### Current user after logout — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/current
